example_quotes: Medical Student: Memory loss or confusion?
Patient: Nope.
Medical Student: And are you allergic to anything?
Patient: No, not that I know.
Medical Student: Changes in your bowel movement or abdominal pain?
Patient: Nope.
Medical Student: Do you find you have any chest pain associated with the shortness of breath?
Patient: Oh no, I don't really have any pains.
Medical Student: So this time around, have you had any fevers?
Patient: I've been having a couple of chills but like they would come and go. I didn't really think it was a fever.
Medical Student: OK, what color is your sputum?
Patient: It's mainly like clear white.
Medical Student: OK yeah so you don't see yellow pus or anything green or bloody in there?
Patient: No, I don't think so. But there's definitely like a lot more than what I usually produce.
Medical Student: Memory loss or confusion?
Patient: Nope.

Patient: Hi, yes I just came in today because I've been a bit concerned about some breathing difficulties over the last few days. It all started out with like a cough over the last week, but now I'm having trouble breathing as well.
Medical Student: So you said a cough as well, so the cough at least a week back and the shortness of breath or difficulty breathing, when did that start?

Patient: So yeah, the cough, I usually have a cough. I've had COPD for a long time, but this past week the coughing has been much worse with a lot of more sputum and. Other than that, it started I would say two to three days ago.
Medical Student: Dizziness or fainting spells?
Patient: No.
Patient: Hi, yes I just came in today because I've been a bit concerned about some breathing difficulties over the last few days.
Medical Student: So you said a cough as well, so the cough at least a week back and the shortness of breath or difficulty breathing, when did that start?
Patient: The cough got worse and then every time I'm moving around I like have to sit down and catch my breath, which is pretty abnormal for me.
Medical Student: OK alright. So this time around, have you had any fevers?
Patient: I've been having a couple of chills but like they would come and go. I didn't really think it was a fever.
Medical Student: OK yeah so you don't see yellow pus or anything green or bloody in there?
Patient: No, I don't think so.
Medical Student: Headaches?
Patient: No headaches.
Medical Student: Any changes in your vision or hearing?
Patient: Nope.
Patient: I do have some high blood pressure which I take, I think I take one of these medications called metoprolol.
Medical Student: OK, and when was the last time you had your blood pressure checked?
Medical Student: Have a stuffy nose or runny nose?
Patient: I do feel a bit stuffy, but it's not too bad.
Medical Student: Do you find you have any chest pain associated with the shortness of breath?
Patient: Oh no, I don't really have any pains.
Medical Student: How about calf pain?
Patient: Nope.
Medical Student: Have a stuffy nose or runny nose?
Patient: I do feel a bit stuffy, but it's not too bad.
Medical Student: And how about smell or taste?
Patient: Umm, no. I think they're the same.
Medical Student: And any swelling in your in your legs or upper limbs?
Patient: No, not that I know.
Medical Student: And how about smell or taste?
Patient: Umm, no. I think they're the same.
Medical Student: Umm, back when I was a kid I had my tonsils removed.
Medical Student: OK, any weight loss?
Patient: No.
Medical Student: Changes to urinating?
Patient: No, that's all fine
Medical Student: Any changes in your vision or hearing?
Patient: Nope.
Patient: I do find myself wheezing a little over the last few days as well.
